---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout>
  <div class="bg-img flex min-h-screen flex-col items-center bg-[#103141]">
    <div
      class="flex w-full flex-col items-center gap-8 px-4 py-12 md:w-3xl md:gap-12 md:px-0 md:py-20"
    >
      <!-- Header -->
      <div class="flex w-full flex-col items-center gap-0">
        <h1 class="font-[Syne] text-2xl font-[800] text-[#EDEBD7] md:text-4xl">
          CAREERS AT OBSERVV
        </h1>
        <p
          class="text-center font-['Crimson_Pro'] text-lg text-[#EDEBD7] opacity-75 md:text-2xl"
        >
          Build the future of autonomous flight.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Culture Section -->
      <div class="flex w-full flex-col items-center gap-4">
        <div class="flex h-full w-full flex-col items-center gap-1">
          <h4
            class="w-full text-left font-['Crimson_Pro'] text-xl text-[#EDEBD7] md:text-3xl"
          >
            What to Expect
          </h4>
          <div class="w-full text-left font-['Crimson_Text'] text-base text-[#EDEBD7] opacity-75 md:text-lg">
            <ul class="list-disc ml-6 space-y-1">
              <li>We are a small team that moves fast and questions every extra gram, rupee, line of code, and step in the process.</li>
              <li>We want to go from whiteboard to flight tests in days.</li>
              <li>We believe in full-ownership. You own your piece of the plane, from napkin sketch to failure report. Launch it, fix it, fly it.</li>
              <li>Our goal is to deliver thousands of autonomous planes that change how the world moves cargo. If what you're doing doesn't get us closer to that, stop doing it.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex h-full w-full flex-col items-center gap-1">
          <h4
            class="w-full text-left font-['Crimson_Pro'] text-xl text-[#EDEBD7] md:text-3xl"
          >
            Why You Might Not Like Working at Observv
          </h4>
          <div class="w-full text-left font-['Crimson_Text'] text-base text-[#EDEBD7] opacity-75 md:text-lg">
            <ul class="list-disc ml-6 space-y-2">
              <li>We work <strong>on-site</strong>, right next to our aircraft and airfield, 6 days a week. There's no remote work here. Building the future means being present, together, at the airfield and in the hangar, every day.</li>
              <li>We don't have middle managers or project babysitters.</li>
              <li>Feedback is direct and appreciated. You'll hear what's working and what isn't—fast.</li>
              <li>We push hard, then we recover. You'll work intensely, but when you're off, you're really off.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex h-full w-full flex-col items-center gap-1">
          <h4
            class="w-full text-left font-['Crimson_Pro'] text-xl text-[#EDEBD7] md:text-3xl"
          >
            TLDR; We Like People Who Are
          </h4>
          <div class="w-full text-left font-['Crimson_Text'] text-base text-[#EDEBD7] opacity-75 md:text-lg">
            <ul class="list-disc ml-6 space-y-1">
              <li>Highly technical</li>
              <li>Highly autonomous (pun intended)</li>
              <li>Highly driven</li>
              <li>High in emotional intelligence (EQ)</li>
              <li>Low in ego</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Job Listings -->
      <div class="flex w-full flex-col items-center gap-6">
        <h2 class="w-full text-center font-['Crimson_Pro'] text-2xl text-[#EDEBD7] md:text-4xl">
          Open Positions
        </h2>

        <!-- Avionics Lead -->
        <div class="w-full rounded-lg border border-[#EDEBD7]/20 bg-[#EDEBD7]/5 p-6">
          <div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
            <div class="flex flex-col gap-1">
              <h3 class="font-['Crimson_Pro'] text-xl font-bold text-[#EDEBD7] md:text-2xl">
                Avionics Lead
              </h3>
              <p class="font-['Crimson_Text'] text-sm text-[#EDEBD7] opacity-60 md:text-base">
                On-Site in Bangalore
              </p>
            </div>
            
            <p class="font-['Crimson_Text'] text-base text-[#EDEBD7] opacity-75 md:text-lg">
              As an early Avionics Engineer at Observv, you will lead the avionics and embedded integration of our autonomous aircraft. The role involves interfacing sensors, navigation systems, and flight controllers within the overall vehicle system.
            </p>

            <div class="flex flex-col gap-3">
              <div>
                <h4 class="font-['Crimson_Pro'] text-lg font-semibold text-[#EDEBD7]">What you'll do</h4>
                <ul class="list-disc ml-6 space-y-1 font-['Crimson_Text'] text-sm text-[#EDEBD7] opacity-75 md:text-base">
                  <li>Integrate onboard avionics with autopilot, navigation, and mission systems</li>
                  <li>Support sensor fusion (GPS, IMU, magnetometers, air data systems)</li>
                  <li>Design and test electrical interfaces using CAN, UART, SPI, and I2C protocols</li>
                  <li>Assist in flight testing and post-mission data evaluation</li>
                  <li>Collaborate with mechanical and software teams to deliver integrated systems</li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <div>
                <h4 class="font-['Crimson_Pro'] text-lg font-semibold text-[#EDEBD7]">What you'll bring</h4>
                <ul class="list-disc ml-6 space-y-1 font-['Crimson_Text'] text-sm text-[#EDEBD7] opacity-75 md:text-base">
                  <li>Hands-on experience with Flight controller and sensor integration</li>
                  <li>Familiarity with MAVLink protocol and embedded systems</li>
                  <li>Knowledge of mechanical interfaces and structural considerations</li>
                  <li>Analytical mindset with attention to system-level integration</li>
                </ul>
                <h5 class="font-['Crimson_Pro'] text-lg font-semibold text-[#EDEBD7]"> PS: We don't care about degrees or credentials. Send us proof of work!</h5>
              </div>

              <div>
                <h4 class="font-['Crimson_Pro'] text-lg font-semibold text-[#EDEBD7]">Ideal Qualifications</h4>
                <ul class="list-disc ml-6 space-y-1 font-['Crimson_Text'] text-sm text-[#EDEBD7] opacity-75 md:text-base">
                  <li>Experience architecting, assembling, and troubleshooting embedded electronic systems on real aircraft (UAVs, drones, GA, or military platforms)</li>
                  <li>Strong grasp of fault-tolerant system design, EMI/EMC best practices, and high-reliability wiring or PCB development</li>
                  <li>Working fluency in reading/debugging schematics and rapidly iterating hardware prototypes</li>
                  <li>Comfortable with both hacking together quick test rigs and seeing hardware/software through certification-level reliability</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="mt-4 flex justify-center">
              <a
                href="https://superform.co/tWX4rgi"
                class="rounded-lg bg-[#EDEBD7] px-6 py-2 font-['Crimson_Pro'] text-base font-semibold text-[#103141] transition-opacity hover:opacity-90"
              >
                Apply for Avionics Lead
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Mechanical Engineer -->
        <div class="w-full rounded-lg border border-[#EDEBD7]/20 bg-[#EDEBD7]/5 p-6">
          <div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
            <div class="flex flex-col gap-1">
              <h3 class="font-['Crimson_Pro'] text-xl font-bold text-[#EDEBD7] md:text-2xl">
                Mechanical Engineer
              </h3>
              <p class="font-['Crimson_Text'] text-sm text-[#EDEBD7] opacity-60 md:text-base">
                On-Site in Bangalore
              </p>
            </div>
            
            <p class="font-['Crimson_Text'] text-base text-[#EDEBD7] opacity-75 md:text-lg">
              As a Mechanical Engineer at Observv, your task would be to help us design, prototype, and manufacture our first aircraft from scratch. You will contribute to the structural and mechanical integration of autonomous aircraft systems while collaborating across avionics, embedded systems, and software domains.
            </p>

            <div class="flex flex-col gap-3">
              <div>
                <h4 class="font-['Crimson_Pro'] text-lg font-semibold text-[#EDEBD7]">What you'll do</h4>
                <ul class="list-disc ml-6 space-y-1 font-['Crimson_Text'] text-sm text-[#EDEBD7] opacity-75 md:text-base">
                  <li>Design and model mechanical and structural components using CAD tools</li>
                  <li>Integrate mechanical components with autopilot systems, sensors, and avionics</li>
                  <li>Conduct UAV assembly, system integration, and flight testing</li>
                  <li>Collaborate with avionics and software teams for system development</li>
                  <li>Perform post-flight data analysis and propose design iterations</li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <div>
                <h4 class="font-['Crimson_Pro'] text-lg font-semibold text-[#EDEBD7]">What you'll bring</h4>
                <ul class="list-disc ml-6 space-y-1 font-['Crimson_Text'] text-sm text-[#EDEBD7] opacity-75 md:text-base">
                  <li>Proficiency in CAD design and mechanical system modeling</li>
                  <li>Familiarity with UAV systems, autopilot, and sensor integration</li>
                  <li>Basic understanding of electrical protocols: CAN, UART, SPI, I2C, MAVLink</li>
                  <li>Strong problem-solving skills and ownership in R&D settings</li>
                </ul>
                <h5 class="font-['Crimson_Pro'] text-lg font-semibold text-[#EDEBD7]"> PS: We don't care about degrees or credentials. Send us proof of work!</h5>
              </div>

              <div>
                <h4 class="font-['Crimson_Pro'] text-lg font-semibold text-[#EDEBD7]">Ideal Qualifications</h4>
                <ul class="list-disc ml-6 space-y-1 font-['Crimson_Text'] text-sm text-[#EDEBD7] opacity-75 md:text-base">
                  <li>Deep understanding of aircraft structural design and practical applications in aerospace contexts</li>
                  <li>Proven experience taking mechanical components from concept to real-world deployment, especially in aviation or similar environments</li>
                  <li>Extensive experience with CAD software for designing complex, interdependent mechanical systems</li>
                  <li>Hands-on experience with machining and fabrication processes, including an intuitive understanding of achievable tolerances</li>
                  <li>Ability to work effectively within a team to collaboratively develop robust, efficient, and integrated solutions</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="mt-4 flex justify-center">
              <a
                href="https://superform.co/cpL2E0b"
                class="rounded-lg bg-[#EDEBD7] px-6 py-2 font-['Crimson_Pro'] text-base font-semibold text-[#103141] transition-opacity hover:opacity-90"
              >
                Apply for Mechanical Engineer
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- UAV Systems Engineer -->
        <div class="w-full rounded-lg border border-[#EDEBD7]/20 bg-[#EDEBD7]/5 p-6">
          <div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
            <div class="flex flex-col gap-1">
              <h3 class="font-['Crimson_Pro'] text-xl font-bold text-[#EDEBD7] md:text-2xl">
                UAV Systems and Operations Engineer
              </h3>
              <p class="font-['Crimson_Text'] text-sm text-[#EDEBD7] opacity-60 md:text-base">
                On-Site in Bangalore • 2+ years experience
              </p>
            </div>
            
            <p class="font-['Crimson_Text'] text-base text-[#EDEBD7] opacity-75 md:text-lg">
              Join our team as a UAV Systems and Operations Engineer with hands-on experience in UAV autonomy, avionics systems and flight operations. You'll be responsible for UAV system design, integration, and critical flight test operations.
            </p>

            <div class="flex flex-col gap-3">
              <div>
                <h4 class="font-['Crimson_Pro'] text-lg font-semibold text-[#EDEBD7]">Requirements</h4>
                <ul class="list-disc ml-6 space-y-1 font-['Crimson_Text'] text-sm text-[#EDEBD7] opacity-75 md:text-base">
                  <li>Experience on UAV avionics systems</li>
                  <li>Proficient with Ardupilot codebase, Companion computers and Mavlink protocol. Capable of configuring, calibrating, operating and tuning UAVs</li>
                  <li>Aeromodelling background with hands-on experience on UAV electronics, embedded systems, communication systems and mechatronic systems</li>
                  <li>Strong fundamentals of UAV systems, sub-system design and system architecture</li>
                  <li>Knowledge and hands-on experience in peripheral systems, sensor systems, sensor redundancy, communication protocols for UAVs</li>
                  <li>Experienced GCS operator (50+ hours), familiar with autonomous UAV operations, and mission planning</li>
                  <li>Critical operations during flight testing, familiar with C-2 callouts</li>
                  <li>Maintain a pre-flight and post-flight checklist</li>
                  <li>Capable of understanding and assessing flight logs for performance, tuning and failures</li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <div>
                <h4 class="font-['Crimson_Pro'] text-lg font-semibold text-[#EDEBD7]">Responsibilities</h4>
                <ul class="list-disc ml-6 space-y-1 font-['Crimson_Text'] text-sm text-[#EDEBD7] opacity-75 md:text-base">
                  <li>UAV system design</li>
                  <li>UAV system integration and configuration</li>
                  <li>GCS operations for flight tests with critical decision making</li>
                  <li>Working on cross-domain aspects</li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <div>
                <h4 class="font-['Crimson_Pro'] text-lg font-semibold text-[#EDEBD7]">Attributes</h4>
                <ul class="list-disc ml-6 space-y-1 font-['Crimson_Text'] text-sm text-[#EDEBD7] opacity-75 md:text-base">
                  <li>Readiness to travel with flexibility on working hours</li>
                  <li>Effective verbal and written communication</li>
                  <li>Experience working in agile R&D environments</li>
                  <li>Commitment to project timelines and cross-functional teamwork</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="mt-4 flex justify-center">
              <a
                href="https://superform.co/doaiHB6"
                class="rounded-lg bg-[#EDEBD7] px-6 py-2 font-['Crimson_Pro'] text-base font-semibold text-[#103141] transition-opacity hover:opacity-90"
              >
                Apply for UAV Systems Engineer
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Application Section -->
      <div class="flex w-full flex-col items-center gap-4">
        <div class="flex h-full w-full flex-col items-center gap-1">
          <h4
            class="w-full text-center font-['Crimson_Pro'] text-xl text-[#EDEBD7] md:text-3xl"
          >
            Ready to Join Us?
          </h4>
          <p
            class="w-full text-center font-['Crimson_Text'] text-base text-[#EDEBD7] opacity-75 md:text-lg"
          >
            If you're excited by this mission but don't tick every box above, we still want to hear from you. We value diverse backgrounds, unorthodox experience, and relentless drive.
          </p>
          <div class="mt-4">
            <a
              href="mailto:khushi@aspera.industries"
              class="rounded-lg bg-[#EDEBD7] px-6 py-3 font-['Crimson_Pro'] text-lg font-semibold text-[#103141] transition-opacity hover:opacity-90"
            >
              Apply Now
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .bg-img {
    background-image: url("/background.png");
    background-size: contain;
    background-position: center;
    background-repeat: repeat;
  }
</style>
